Others: The Celtics played a strong first half but struggled in the second half, losing 105-92 to the Thunder.
Jayson Tatum had 26 points and 10 rebounds for the Celtics, while Jaylen Brown added 21 points.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander finished with 33 points and 11 rebounds for the Thunder.
The Thunder improved to 30-5 with their 15th straight victory.
The Celtics dropped to 26-10 with the loss.
The Celtics will finish their four-game road trip by taking on the Nuggets at 10 p.m. Tuesday in Denver.
